{
  "text": "The roles of social interactions in CBGEP have been noted to add to participants' networks and serve as a source of support, enjoyment and belonging [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . This study corroborated these findings indicating that there was strong support for the social features of CBGEP in aiding participant adherence. The social, group dynamic of the programmes added to participants' wellbeing by providing social, supportive environments which offered a means for older people to maintain social connectivity over the latter part of their lives. Maintaining these connections is important because there are increased health risks related to social isolation [CITATION_4] .",
